<h2>DOM (Document Object Model )</h2>
        <p class = "content-p">
            The DOM is a W3C (World Wide Web Consortium) standard. The Document Object Model is a cross platform and 
            language independent application programing interface. DOM treats a documents (HTML, XML or XHTL) as a tree structure.
            Each part of a document (which is called as a node) is an object of DOM. This objects can be manipulated programatically. 
            and the visible changes will be reflected in the document view. 
        </p>
        <P>
          <h3>DOM Types</h3>
          The W3C DOM standard is separated into 3 different parts:
          <ul>
            <li>Core DOM - standard model for all document types</li>
            <li>XML DOM - standard model for XML documents</li>
            <li>HTML DOM - standard model for HTML documents</li>
          </ul>
        </P>
        <p>
          <h3>An XML document sample</h3>
          <div class="code-div col-lg-10 col-md-12 col-sm-12 card border-info ">

                &ensp;&lt;/name><br><br>
                &ensp;&lt;phone><br>
                  &ensp; &ensp; &lt;mobile>&lt;/mobile><br>
                &ensp;&lt;/phone><br><br>

                &ensp;&lt;/dob><br><br>
